PackageKit Release Notes

1. Write NEWS entries for gnome-color-manager in the same format as usual.

Version 3.3.1
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Released: 2011-xx-xx

* Translations
* New Features:
* Bugfix:

git shortlog GNOME_COLOR_MANAGER_3_3_0.. | grep -i -v trivial | grep -v Merge | uniq > NEWS.new

3. Commit changes in gnome-color-manager git:

git commit -a -m "Release version 3.3.1"
git tag -s GNOME_COLOR_MANAGER_3_3_1 -m "==== Version 3.3.1 ===="
<enter password>
git push --tags
git push

4. Create tarball

make distcheck

5. Upload tarballs:

scp *.tar.xz rhughes@master.gnome.org:

6. Install module

ssh rhughes@master.gnome.org
ftpadmin install gnome-color-manager-*.tar.xz

7. Do post release version bump in configure.ac

8. Commit trivial changes:

git commit -a -m "trivial: Post release version bump"
git push

9. Send an email to gnome-color-manager-list@gnome.org

gnome-color-manager is a session program that makes it easy to manage, install
and generate color profiles in the GNOME desktop.

